731751f-a.title: Fires, accidents and tragedies - [Elevated railroad accident.]
731751f-a.text:
Fires, Accidents and Tragedies: An Elevated
Railroad accident on Ntnth Avenue, at West 53rd Street.
The photographer is viewing southeastward
from a rooftop on the west side of the Avenue. Buildings
shown on the east side of same, from 53rd (left) to 52nd
(right) Street's.
September 11, 1905
Gustave Scholer M. D.
Gift Thru New York Historical Society
MAY BE REPROUCED

731752f-a.title: Fires, accidents and tragedies - [Elevated railroad accident.]
731752f-a.text:
Elevated R.R. tragedy at Ninth Ave., and 53rd Street, Monday morning
September 11th., 1905. Twelve persons were killed, and forty-eight
injured. Fortunately for the early hour; or this might have proven one of
the major disasters in New York City's history.
SeDtember 11, 1905.
Gustav Scholer, N.D.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
766  NEG ~:.
